begin
reserve i for (Element of ( NAT ));
reserve j for (Element of ( NAT ));
reserve k for (Element of ( NAT ));
reserve n for (Element of ( NAT ));
reserve l for (Element of ( NAT ));
reserve D for non empty set;
reserve A for (Matrix of n,D);
theorem
((((((A is  line_circulant & [ i,j ] in [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :]) & k = ( i + 1 )) & l = ( j + 1 )) & i < n) & j < n) implies ( A * (i,j) ) = ( A * (k,l) ))
proof
assume that
A1: A is  line_circulant
and
A2: [ i,j ] in [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :]
and
A3: k = ( i + 1 )
and
A4: l = ( j + 1 )
and
A5: i < n
and
A6: j < n;
consider p being (FinSequence of D) such that ( len p ) = ( width A ) and A7: A is_line_circulant_about p by A1,CKB7:def 1;
A8: ( Indices A ) = [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
j in ( Seg n ) by A2,ZFMISC_1:87;
then 1 <= j by FINSEQ_1:1;
then ( 1 + 1 ) <= ( j + 1 ) by XREAL_1:6;
then A9: 1 <= ( j + 1 ) by XXREAL_0:2;
( j + 1 ) <= n by A6,INT_1:7;
then A10: l in ( Seg n ) by A4,A9;
i in ( Seg n ) by A2,ZFMISC_1:87;
then 1 <= i by FINSEQ_1:1;
then ( 1 + 1 ) <= ( i + 1 ) by XREAL_1:6;
then A11: 1 <= ( i + 1 ) by XXREAL_0:2;
( i + 1 ) <= n by A5,INT_1:7;
then k in ( Seg n ) by A3,A11;
then [ k,l ] in ( Indices A ) by A8,A10,ZFMISC_1:87;
then ( A * (k,l) ) = ( p . ( ( ( l - k ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) by A7,CKB6:def 1
.= ( p . ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) by A3,A4
.= ( A * (i,j) ) by A2,A7,A8,CKB6:def 1;
hence thesis;
end;
